{"created":"2014-10-02T20:49:39+00:00","modified":"2015-04-30T19:46:13+00:00","valid":{"from":"2013-04-25T20:42:14+00:00","to":"3013-04-25T20:42:14+00:00"},"hreflang":"en","guid":"dc515e5d-4e96-454b-8752-a7154e9f2e0b","title":"Sound Opinions Show 387, April 26, 2013","teaser":"Producer Joe Boyd remembers making studio magic with legendary UK songwriter Nick Drake. Plus, Jim and Greg review the new album from Canadian shoegazers The Besnard Lakes.","description":"   NEWS:\nA number of musical figures died this week including folk singer Richie Havens, Parliament Funkadelic bassist Cordell &ldquo;Boogie&rdquo; Mosson, Divinyls singer Chrissie Amphlett and Game Theory frontman Scott Miller. In memory of Miller hosts Jim DeRogatis and Greg Kot play &ldquo;Regenisraen&rdquo; from Game Theory&rsquo;s 1986 release The Big Shot Chronicles.\nFEATURE:\nVeteran producer Joe Boyd joins Jim and Greg to talk about the life and legacy of British singer/songwriter Nick Drake. Boyd discovered Drake in the late 1960&rsquo;s and produced his first two albums, Five Leaves Left in 1969 and Bryter Layter in 1970. Pink Moon would follow in 1972, and unfortunately that would be Drake&rsquo;s final contribution to music before he overdosed on anti-depressants at age 26. Drake achieved mainstream success posthumously after &ldquo;Pink Moon&rdquo; was prominently used in a Volkswagen commercial in 1999. Joe Boyd pays tribute to Nick Drake on the new album Way to Blue, which features live covers by Robyn Hitchcock, Vashti Bunyan and Teddy Thompson, the son of Richard and Linda Thompson.\nREVIEW:\nJim and Greg review Until in Excess, Imperceptible UFO, the fourth release form Montreal shoegazers The Besnard Lakes.\nDESERT ISLAND JUKEBOX:\nJim goes back to 1994 for his Desert Island Jukebox selection. He adds &ldquo;Seether&rdquo; by the alt rock group Veruca Salt. Frontwomen Louise Post and Nina Gordon recently announced they were burying the hatchet and reuniting.&nbsp;\n","contentencoded":"<!